---
title: Creamy Potato Cod Cakes with Green Salad and Lemon Aioli
description: Think of these as a swankier, more sophisticated version of fish sticks. You’ve still got flaky, tender fish in a crispy breaded coating. But when shaped into patties with creamy potatoes and peppy Cajun spices mixed in, they somehow seem extra elegant. If you want to get fancy and call them croquettes, go right ahead.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/creamy-potato-cod-cakes-8b36b218.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/creamy-potato-cod-cakes-b6bebd93.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 580 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 240 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-potato-cod-cakes-59669b4ac6243b34f02c0513
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce}, then dice into ½-inch
cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 1 inch. Bring
to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, ~{10-15%minutes}. Drain.

Trim, then finely chop @scallions{2}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve
@lemon{1}; cut one half into wedges. Pat @cod fillets{11%ounce} dry with a #paper
towel{}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
a pinch of garlic, and a squeeze of lemon. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and
more lemon and garlic (to taste, but save a little garlic for the potatoes). Set
aside.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in #pot{} used for potatoes over medium-low heat. Add
scallions and remaining garlic. Cook, tossing, until scallions are softened and
garlic is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Return potatoes to pot and mash with a
#potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from
heat.

Add cod to mashed potatoes in pot along with @Cajun spice blend{2%teaspoon}
(we sent more). Stir to combine. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} to a #shallow
dish{}. Season with remaining @Cajun spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.
Using wet hands, shape cod mixture into 4 equally-sized cakes. Press cakes into
panko, turning to coat all over.

> TIP: Planning ahead? Let the cakes chill in the fridge until firm,
~{15-30%minutes}.

Heat @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a
#nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add cod cakes and cook until browned and crisped,
~{5-7%minutes} per side, flipping them over carefully.

> TIP: Add another drizzle of oil if the pan seems dry.

Toss @arugula{2%ounce}, a drizzle of @vegetable oil{3%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of
lemon juice in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide cod cakes
between #plates{}, then dollop with aioli. Serve with salad on the side and lemon
wedges for squeezing over.